  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "Vårdberget is located in the centre of Ljusne, 13 km from Söderhamn.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Vårdberget is located in the middle of Ljusne, 13 km from Söderhamn.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          }
        },
        "kommunikationer": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Access",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "By car: From Söderhamn, head towards Sandarne. From there, go towards Ljusne and turn left at the sign \"Mot Ljusne bruk\". You will see the crag as you drive through Ljusne. Just before the ICA supermarket, at the intersection of Smedsvägen/Nygatan, turn left and park right below the crag. At the parking area, there’s an old wooden fence. Go through a hole in it and walk up a bit, following the fence for about 30 m. Here, there is a six-metre high wall with four cracks. GPS coordinates: Lat: N 61º 12' 40.60\" Long: E 17º 7' 55.4\".",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          }
        },
        "historik": {
          "title": {
            "text": "History",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vaggar": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Walls",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          }
        },
        "tuggummiblocket": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Gum Block",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Counting from the left:",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          }
        },
        "chokladblocket": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Chocolate Block",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "To reach the Chocolate Block, follow the fence until it veers towards the top. From here, walk towards the large factory along the coastline until the factory disappears behind the treetops, then you will see a pointed boulder below you. When you turn around the corner, the wall of the Chocolate Block appears. The routes here vary in length between 5 and 7 m.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vattencisternen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Water Cistern",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "At the top of the crag, towards the village, there is a large water cistern. Walk 15 m from the cistern towards a telephone pole and in the direction of a yellow apartment building. One of the guy wires on the pole is anchored with a large bolt that can be used as a rappel bolt for descending to the routes on the north side of the crag. You would rappel directly over \"Heaven up here\". If you prefer not to rappel down, you can walk down to the left along a ramp.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:vardberget-halsingland"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
